ROW.GraphMat_Title: Paintings central apse - Vault - Maiestas Domini
ROW.Author: Gaetano Alfano
ROW.Description: Depiction of the “Maiestas Domini” presiding from the vault the main apse. This central figure, enclosed in a mandorla and heavily deteriorated, is surrounded by the four living creatures, also known as the Tetramorph, strategically positioned at the corners of the vault.

ROW.GraphMat_Title: Paintings central apse - vault - Maiestas Domini
ROW.Author: Gaetano Alfano

ROW.GraphMat_Title: Paintings central apse - vault and south wall
ROW.Author: Gaetano Alfano
ROW.File_Name: GM000023-Paintings central apse-vault and south wall.jpg

ROW.Author: Gaetano Alfano
ROW.Description: Adoration of the (not preserved) Lamb by the twenty-four elders of the Apocalypse.These figures of the elders, of which only half are preserved and in a rather fragmentary state, are arranged around an empty throne with the scroll of the seven seals on a cushion. Below, the hand of God, flanked by two birds, is depicted in the axial window.

ROW.Author: Gaetano Alfano
ROW.Description: Feigned curtain; dado decoration; ornamental decoration

ROW.Author: Gaetano Alfano
ROW.Description: Detail of the bottom register with five of the elders of the Apocalypse making a gesture of adoration. The figures are seated on high-backed chairs and carry a viola in their right hand.
